<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1155,1597,1727]" lastBlockId="18.[160,1156,142,305]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="1550" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549">
<taxonomicName authority="Olssoni 1944" authorityName="Olssoni" authorityYear="1944" box="[160,552,1634,1658]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Incacardium">
<emphasis box="[160,252,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549">Cardium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[266,398,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549">Incacardium</emphasis>
) Olsson, 1944
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to the Cretaceous genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Scotti 1978" authorityName="Scotti" authorityYear="1978" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Pleuriocardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1155,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549">Pleuriocardia</emphasis>
Scott, 1978
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schneider JA" box="[331,517,1669,1693]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1549" pagination="321 - 346" refId="ref26260" refString="Schneider JA. 1995. Phylogeny of the Cardiidae (Molluscai Bivalvia): Protocardiinaei Laevicardiinaei Lahilliinaei Tulongocardiinae subfam. n. and Pleuriocardiinae subfam. n. Zool Scr. 24 (4): 321 - 346." type="journal article" year="1995">Schneider (1995)</bibRefCitation>
based on the shared characters of symmetrical, concavedown, triangular spines rising from the middle of radial ribs and the shape or orientation of the right anterior cardinal tooth and right posterior cardinal socket. Neither hinge character can be confirmed for the Caballas Formation specimens. 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Olssoni" authorityYear="1944" box="[788,1081,177,201]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Pleuriocardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Incacardium">
<emphasis box="[788,927,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550">Pleuriocardia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[940,1072,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550">Incacardium</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
differs from two other pleuriocardine subgenera, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scotti" authorityYear="1978" box="[726,865,212,236]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Pleuriocardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[726,865,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550">Pleuriocardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[890,923,212,236]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Scotti 1978" authorityName="Scotti" authorityYear="1978" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Pleuriocardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Venerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dochmocardia">
<emphasis box="[1016,1155,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550">Pleuriocardia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[167,324,246,270]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550">Dochmocardia</emphasis>
) Scott, 1978
</taxonomicName>
, by having triangular radial ribs, rather than rounded radial ribs, and by having a posteroventrally directed broad sulcus (
<bibRefCitation author="Olsson AA" box="[833,968,281,305]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1550" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref25769" refString="Olsson AA. 1944. Contributions to the Tertiary paleontology of northern Peru. Part VII. The Cretaceous of the Paita region. Bulletins Am Paleontol. 19 (68): 1 - 147." type="journal article" year="1944">Olsson 1944</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
